Shareholders of the Utheri wa Lari in Maai Mahiu, Naivasha constituency, yesterday asked the government to warn Maasai morans not to invade their farms.Chairman Stephen Muiru said about 400 cattle were driven into their farms on Tuesday last week, where they destroyed 50 acres of maize.He said the morans, armed with arrows and spears, stood guard as the cattle destroyed the maize. Kiambu Senator Kimani Wamatangi said the shareholders have struggled to reclaim their land.He urged the government to protect the farmers.